title: Kubernetes namespaces
agents: linux
author: Henri Wahl <henri@nagstamon.de>
catalog: generic
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the status of Kubernetes namespace resources on nodes where the agent plugin
 is deployed. The plugin collects data from the local Kubernetes cluster using {kubectl} commands
 and does not require any additional installation on the cluster itself.

 The check monitors the following Kubernetes resources within namespaces:

 - {CronJobs}: Monitors the number of active CronJob instances. Returns {WARN}/{CRIT} if the number
   of active jobs exceeds configurable thresholds (default: 2/3).

 - {DaemonSets}: Monitors the scheduling status of DaemonSets. Returns {CRIT} if any pods are unavailable.
   Tracks current number scheduled, desired number scheduled, number ready, and number unavailable.

 - {Deployments}: Monitors deployment replica status. Returns {CRIT} if not all replicas are ready.
   Tracks total replicas, ready replicas, and unavailable replicas.

 - {PersistentVolumes}: Monitors the capacity usage of persistent volumes. Returns {WARN}/{CRIT} if
   usage exceeds configurable percentage thresholds (default: 80%/90%). Displays used space, total
   capacity, and usage percentage in human-readable format.

 - {Pods}: Monitors pod container states across the namespace. Returns {CRIT} if any containers are
   in a crashing state. Aggregates counts of running, waiting, terminated, and crashing containers.

 - {ReplicaSets}: Monitors replica set status. Returns {CRIT} if not all replicas are ready.
   Tracks total replicas, ready replicas, and unavailable replicas.


